summary: This is a forwarded email from CBP's automated system to the FBI, notifying them of a 'query hit' on Ghislaine Maxwell's travel/identity record (TECSID: P3O92965500A01) by a targeting center user on March 9, 2021. It indicates law enforcement monitoring of Maxwell's movements or records.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The subject of a U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) Person Lookout Query hit, with her record being accessed by the NAIL Targeting Center in Reston.

events.title: CBP Query Hit on Ghislaine Maxwell
events.description: U.S. Customs and Border Protection's automated system generated a notification that Ghislaine Maxwell's record (TECSID: P3O92965500A01) was viewed by a user from the hit list of a query at the CBP-Reston NAIL Targeting Center.

keyFacts: On March 9, 2021, U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) generated an automated alert that Ghislaine Maxwell's record was accessed via a 'Person Lookout Query'.
The query was executed from the CBP-Reston NAIL Targeting Center, indicating active law enforcement interest in Maxwell's travel or identity records.
The notification was sent from a CBP 'do not reply' address to an FBI recipient, showing inter-agency communication regarding Maxwell.
Maxwell's unique identifier in the system was TECSID: P3O92965500A01.
